DIGEST
SB 504 Original 2026 Regular Session Carter
Present law provides that every student, by the end of the 8th grade, must begin to develop
an Individual Graduation Plan or Individualized Education Program, if applicable, to guide
the next academic year's course work and assist in exploring educational and career
